olive oil
1 packet flaked almonds
1 tomato
1 stalk celery
1 packet ciabatta
1 packet chicken breast
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 bag salad leaves
1 packet Creamy Salad Dressing
1 drizzle balsamic vinegar
2 clove garlic

• Roughly chop tomato. Thinly slice celery. Finely
chop garlic. Cut or tear ciabatta into bite-sized
chunks. Cut chicken breast into 2cm chunks.
• In a medium bowl, combine chicken, garlic &
herb seasoning, a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch
of salt and pepper.

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat.
Toast flaked almonds until golden, 2-3 minutes.
Transfer to a bowl and set aside.

• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a
generous drizzle of olive oil. Cook ciabatta until
golden and slightly crispy, 4-5 minutes.
• Add garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
Season to taste. Transfer to a large bowl.

• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a
drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, cook chicken,
tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked
through, 5-6 minutes.

• To the bowl with the croutons, add salad leaves,
tomato, celery, croutons, a drizzle of balsamic
vinegar and olive oil. Toss to combine and
season to taste.

• Divide crouton salad between bowls. Top with
garlic chicken.
• Drizzle over creamy salad dressing.
• Sprinkle with toasted almonds. Enjoy!